Citation.sAbstract: Isothermal vapor-liquid equilibrium data for the binary mixture of 1,1,1,2-tetrafluoroethane (HFC-134a) + normal  butane (R600) were measured at 273.15, 283.15, 293.15, 303.15, 313.15, and 323.15 K, respectively. The  experiments were carried out using a continuous circulation-type equilibrium apparatus to measure temperature,  pressure, and the compositions of the liquid and vapor phases. The experimental data were correlated with the  Peng-Robinson equation of state (PR EOS) using the Wong-Sandler (W-S) mixing rule. Calculated results  showed good agreement with experimental data. It was found that this system has very strong positive azeotropes  for all the temperature ranges studied here.
Citation.sTitle: Vapor-Liquid Equilibria for the 1,1,1,2-Tetrafluoroethane (HFC-134a) + n-Butane (R-600) System
